			<div class="commenttext">
			<p>On the subject of salt, I have had problems with high blood pressure (but it&#8217;s normal now). Do I use salt? Yes! Salting your food isn&#8217;t nearly as bad as you might think, and you&#8217;ll use much less than you probably realize.</p>
<p>Having read numerous books/articles/etc. on the subject (since I&#8217;ve had high bp for years), the majority of sodium (70% according to a couple of books I read) in the average diet doesn&#8217;t come from salting your food; it comes from prepared food. This runs the gamut from frozen (or canned) stuff you buy at the store all the way to dinner at your favorite restaurant (chain places and fast food are bad, but good independent restaurants aren&#8217;t innocent either).</p>
<p>Check your labels! However, if you&#8217;re making food at home, you should be able to season it to taste without worrying too much.</p>
