			<div class="commenttext">
			<p>Lisa &#8211; The quick answer is that brining meat means soaking it in a saline solution to impart moisture and flavor to the meat. It&#8217;s particularly important for lean meats that tend to try out during cooking, like pork and the breast meats of poultry.</p>
<p>You might also check out <a href=http://www.virtualweberbullet.com/brining.html rel="nofollow">this All About Brining</a> page, or the <a href=http://www.foodnetwork.com/food/recipes/recipe/0,,FOOD_9936_8389,00.html rel="nofollow">Good Eats recipe</a> that got me hooked on brining.</p>
			</div>
			
